geneVariantDescriptions.description: EGFR T790M is a gatekeeper mutation that lies within the ATP-binding pocket in the protein kinase domain of the Egfr protein (PMID: 20026433). T790M results in increased Egfr kinase activity, is transforming in culture (PMID: 30952700), and frequently occurrs as secondary somatic mutation that confers resistance to reversible tyrosine kinase inhibitors (PMID: 17671201, PMID: 18227510, PMID: 20026433).
